      "<li><strong>Idle Hands</strong> â€“ Too goofy for a Top 10 spot for me, but itâ€™s harmless fun that takes place on Halloween and it scratches the late-90s teen movie itch that I have sometimes, being a late-90s teen myself</li><li><strong>Phenomena</strong> â€“ Dario Argentoâ€™s giallo sensibilities fused with slasher tropes and supernatural powers.. what else can there be in life?</li><li><strong>The El Duce Tapes</strong> â€“ Itâ€™s gross, a little disturbing and insane.. but super fascinating to me.  I donâ€™t think it glorifies the disgusting nature of the subject(s), otherwise itâ€™d be a harder watch for me because.. like I said.. they are pretty gross</li><li><strong>The Ides of March</strong>â€“ Maybe itâ€™s because Iâ€™m fairly fresh off of watching this one, but itâ€™s a great cast, great visuals and smart writing (at least from my dumb not-politically-savvy perspective)</li>",
